99 A.3d 288 ATTORNEY GRIEVANCE COMMISSION OF MARYLAND v. Thomas Wesley FELDER, II. Misc. Docket AG No. 33,

Sept. Term, 2013.

Court of Appeals of Maryland. Sept. 11, 2014. Caroll G. Bonayre, Assistant Bar Counsel (Glenn M. Gross-man, Bar Counsel, Attorney Grievance Commission of Maryland), for petitioner. Thomas Wesley Felder, II, pro se. Argued before HARRELL, BATTAGLIA, GREENE, ADKINS, McDonald, WATTS, IRMA S. RAKER (Retired, Specially Assigned), JJ. PER CURIAM

ORDER.

For reasons to be stated in an opinion later to be filed, it is this 11th day September, 2014,

ORDERED, by the Court of Appeals of Maryland, that the Respondent, Thomas Wesley Felder, II, be, and he is hereby, disbarred, effective immediately, from the further practice of law in the State of Maryland; and it is further

ORDERED that the Clerk of this Court shall strike the name of Thomas Wesley Felder, II from the register of attorneys, and pursuant to Maryland Rule 16-760(e), shall certify that fact to the Trustees of the Client Protection Fund and the clerks of all judicial tribunals in the State; and it is further

ORDERED that respondent shall pay all costs as taxed by the Clerk of this Court, including the costs of all transcripts, *32pursuant to Maryland Rule 16-761(b), for which sum judgment is entered in favor of the Attorney Grievance Commission of Maryland against Thomas Wesley Felder, II.
